1 AN ACT relating to recyclers and declaring an emergency.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 433.900 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in Sections 1 to 12 of this Act[KRS 433.900 to 433.906], unless the context
5 otherwise requires:
6 (1) "Applicant" means a secondary metals recycler seeking an application for a license
7 with the commission[certificate of registration with the Department of Professional
8 Licensing of the Public Protection Cabinet, as provided in KRS 433.902]. If the
9 secondary metals recycler is owned by a corporation, limited liability company,
10 partnership, limited partnership, incorporated association, or any other entity
11 organized for the purpose of engaging in business as a secondary metals recycler,
12 "applicant" means the officers of these entities;
13 (2) "Commission" means the Motor Vehicle Commission;
14 (3) "Ferrous metals" means any metal containing significant quantities of iron or steel;
15 (4)[(3)] "Name-based background check" means a statewide search of the
16 centralized criminal history record information system by the Department of
17 Kentucky State Police, utilizing the name, date of birth, and Social Security
18 number of the applicant;
19 (5) "Nonferrous metals" means metal not containing significant quantities of iron,
20 including but not limited to copper, brass, aluminum, bronze, lead, zinc, nickel, and
21 alloys thereof, such as any copper or bronze wire, power inverters, bars, pipes,
22 rods, tubing, and wire or cable or coaxial cable of the type used by public utilities,
23 common carriers, or telecommunication services providers;
24 (6)[(4) "Name-based background check" means a statewide search of the centralized
25 criminal history record information system by the Department of Kentucky State
26 Police, utilizing the name, date of birth, and Social Security number of the
27 applicant;
