9 SECTION 7. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 433 IS CREATED TO
10 READ AS FOLLOWS:
11 A secondary metals recycler shall at all times maintain in a prominent place in its place
12 of business a notice in two (2) inch lettering that states the secondary metals recycler's
13 usual business hours and includes the following language:
14 "A PERSON ATTEMPTING TO SELL ANY REGULATED MATERIAL MUST
15 PRESENT SUFFICIENT IDENTIFICATION AND WRITTEN PROOF OF
16 OWNERSHIP REQUIRED BY STATE LAW.
17 WARNING: STATE LAW PROVIDES A CRIMINAL PENALTY FOR A PERSON
18 WHO PROVIDES A FALSE IDENTIFICATION DOCUMENT OR OTHER FALSE
19 INFORMATION TO A SECONDARY METALS RECYCLER WHILE ATTEMPTING
20 TO SELL ANY REGULATED MATERIAL."
21 SECTION 8. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 433 IS CREATED TO
22 READ AS FOLLOWS:
23 (1) A law enforcement agency shall provide to each secondary metals recycler within
24 the agency's jurisdiction a searchable electronic list of persons convicted of theft
25 or receiving stolen property. The list shall be prepared in accordance with rules
26 adopted by the law enforcement agency and shall be updated monthly. The law
27 enforcement agency may request the appropriate Circuit Court clerk to provide
