14 persons from the time of its recording and shall bear interest thereafter until paid.
15 The lien created shall take precedence over all other liens, except state, county,
16 school board, and city taxes, except as provided in subsection (10) of this section.
17 The local government shall possess the lien for ten (10) years following the date of
18 the final, nonappealable order of a code enforcement board or final judgment of the
19 court. The lien may be enforced by judicial proceeding.
20 (10) The lien provided in subsection (9) of this section shall not take precedence or
21 priority over a previously recorded lien if:
22 (a) The local government failed to provide the lien holder a copy of the
23 determination in accordance with subsection (8) of this section; or
24 (b) The lien holder received a copy of the determination as required by subsection
25 (8) of this section, and the lien holder corrected the violations or paid all civil
26 fines assessed for the violation and all charges and fees incurred by the local
27 government in connection with the enforcement of the ordinance, including
Page 49 of 53
BR123800.100 - 1238 - XXXX 3/11/2026 3:19 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1238
1 abatement costs.
2 (11) In addition to the remedy prescribed in subsection (7) of this section or any other
3 remedy authorized by law, the owner of a premises upon which a lien has been
4 attached pursuant to this section shall be personally liable for the amount of the
5 lien, including all civil fines assessed for the violation and all charges, fees, and
6 abatement costs incurred by the local government in connection with the
7 enforcement of the ordinance. The local government may bring a civil action
8 against the owner and shall have the same remedies as provided for the recovery of
9 a debt owed. The failure of a local government to comply with subsection (8) of this
10 section, and the failure of a lien to take precedence over previously filed liens as
11 provided in subsection (10) of this section, shall not limit or restrict any remedies
12 that the local government has against the owner of the premises.
13 (12) [The provisions of ]Subsections (7), (9), and (11) of this section shall not apply to
14 an owner, occupant, or person having control or management of any land located in
15 an unincorporated area if the owner, occupant, or person is not the generator of the
16 rubbish or is not dumping or knowingly allowing the dumping of the rubbish and
17 has made reasonable efforts to prevent the dumping of rubbish by other persons
18 onto the premises.
19 (13) [The provisions of ]This section shall not be enforced by a county government upon
20 any premises situated in an unincorporated portion of the county that is assessed as
21 agricultural land for tax purposes by the property valuation administrator.
22 (14) The right to request a hearing pursuant to this section shall be limited to a period of
23 thirty (30) days after notice has been placed on the property and has been sent by
24 certified mail return receipt requested.
