3 Section 34. KRS 16.066 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The Department of Kentucky State Police shall design the electronic and paper
5 forms utilized in subsection[KRS 433.890] (1) of Section 10 of this Act and any
6 other forms and instructions necessary to implement Section 10 of this Act[KRS
7 433.890].
8 (2) The Department of Kentucky State Police shall make the forms and instructions
9 utilized in subsection (1) of this section available on the department's Internet Web
10 site for downloading by any person.
11 (3) The Department of Kentucky State Police shall make single copies of the forms and
12 instructions utilized in subsection (1) of this section available as public records, at
13 the same rate charged for other public records. The department shall not be required
14 to make multiple copies of the forms or instructions for any person, but may do so
15 at the same rate charged for other public records.
16 (4) Any person may make copies of the forms and instructions required by subsection
17 (1) of this section and may charge for the copies. No person, other than the
18 Commonwealth, shall apply for a copyright on the forms or instructions provided
19 by the Department of Kentucky State Police. The Department of Kentucky State
20 Police may, in the name of the Commonwealth, apply for a copyright on the forms
21 and instructions which it produces pursuant to this section.
22 (5) A purchaser required to generate, maintain, and transmit records pursuant to
23 Section 10 of this Act[KRS 433.890]:
24 (a) 1. May utilize the forms designed by the Department of Kentucky State
25 Police; or
26 2. May generate his or her own forms which shall contain at least the
27 information required by Section 10 of this Act[KRS 433.890] and which
