7 Section 35. KRS 65.871 is amended to read as follows:
8 A city, county, urban-county, charter county, unified county, or consolidated local
9 government may adopt an ordinance relating to the purchase of metals and metal-
10 containing products provided the ordinance:
11 (1) Contains at least the provisions specified in KRS 15.232, 16.066, 433.892[433.890]
12 to 433.896, Sections 1 to 12 of this Act[433.900 to 433.906], and 512.090, but
13 which may contain additional provisions; and
14 (2) Does not specify a lesser penalty for a similar offense than specified in KRS
15 15.232, 16.066, 433.892[433.890] to 433.896, and 512.090 or provides that the
16 penalty specified in KRS 433.892[433.890] to 433.896 and 512.090 shall apply.
17 Section 36. The following KRS sections are repealed:
18 177.905 Definitions for KRS 177.910 to 177.950.
19 177.920 Permit fee -- Renewal -- Proceeds.
20 Section 37. To allow time to obtain licenses under this Act and notwithstanding
21 Sections 2, 3, 17, and 18 of this Act or any other provision of this Act that may be
22 construed to require a license to engage in business in this Commonwealth, a secondary
23 metals recycler that has a certificate of registration issued by the Department of
24 Professional Licensing of the Public Protection Cabinet or an automobile, vehicle, or
25 machinery recycler, or material recycler that has a permit from the Department of
26 Highways may continue to engage in business in this Commonwealth for a period not to
27 exceed 90 days following the effective date of this Act.
Page 52 of 53
BR123800.100 - 1238 - XXXX 3/11/2026 3:19 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1238
1 Section 38. A secondary metals recycler shall surrender to the Department of
2 Professional Licensing of the Public Protection Cabinet a certificate of registration issued
3 by the department within 30 days of receipt of a license from the Motor Vehicle
4 Commission. If the application for a license is denied, the secondary metals recycler shall
5 immediately surrender the certificate of registration to the department.
6 Section 39. An automobile, vehicle, or machinery recycler, or material recycler
7 shall surrender to the Department of Highways a permit issued by the department within
8 30 days of receipt of a license from the Motor Vehicle Commission. If the application for
9 a license is denied, the automobile, vehicle, or machinery recycler, or material recycler
10 shall immediately surrender the permit to the department.
11 Section 40. Whereas the Commonwealth has a duty to ensure the proper
12 licensure of regulated industries, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes
13 effect upon its passage and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a
14 law.
